message.content: A gar is a predatory fish found primarily in freshwater habitats. It has a long, slender body covered in bony scales. The scales have a rough, textured surface and are typically brown or green in color. The head of a gar is elongated and pointed, with sharp teeth for catching prey. The eyes are positioned towards the top of the head, giving the gar a good view of its surroundings. Gars can often be found lurking in shallow waters near vegetation, where they prey on smaller fish and crustaceans. In some regions, gars are considered a game fish and are sought after by anglers.
